00:43:25,215 --> 00:43:26,967
What's it look like?

572
00:43:27,050 --> 00:43:29,344
You seeing this, Sarge?

573
00:43:29,428 --> 00:43:31,221
Christ sakes,
leave the man alone.

574
00:43:32,639 --> 00:43:34,474
You can't be serious, bro.

575
00:43:34,558 --> 00:43:37,811
I'm on a chopper back
to Bagram in a couple hours.

576
00:43:37,895 --> 00:43:39,980
No way.

577
00:43:40,063 --> 00:43:42,274
What about the Pakistan border,
patrolling the airwaves?

578
00:43:42,357 --> 00:43:45,611
It's all on automatic
collection now.

579
00:43:45,694 --> 00:43:47,946
What about your boss?
He's still out there somewhere.

580
00:43:48,030 --> 00:43:49,698
You can't... you can't just
give up on him.

581
00:43:49,781 --> 00:43:52,200
- He's been released.
- When?

582
00:43:52,284 --> 00:43:53,577
This morning.

583
00:43:55,746 --> 00:43:57,289
That's fucked up.

584
00:43:57,372 --> 00:43:58,665
Soto, relax.

585
00:43:58,749 --> 00:43:59,499
You're gonna give
yourself a stroke.

586
00:43:59,583 --> 00:44:01,668
- Get over it.
- You get over it.

587
00:44:01,752 --> 00:44:05,213
Haven't you noticed?
Dude's been here a week.

588
00:44:05,297 --> 00:44:08,759
Not a single IED, RPG, mortar,
rocket, sniper, nothing.

589
00:44:10,218 --> 00:44:11,136
I'm not saying it ain't weird.

590
00:44:11,219 --> 00:44:13,889
It's weirder than weird.

591
00:44:13,972 --> 00:44:16,350
We shouldn't even
be talking about it.

592
00:44:16,433 --> 00:44:19,311
Well, nobody's going
anywhere anyhow.

593
00:44:19,394 --> 00:44:20,604
How's that?

594
00:44:20,687 --> 00:44:21,813
We got some weather coming in.

595
00:44:21,897 --> 00:44:24,191
What?

596
00:44:24,274 --> 00:44:26,276
Yeah, it's gonna get nasty.

597
00:44:26,360 --> 00:44:28,320
All air traffic in
the mountains is grounded.

598
00:44:28,403 --> 00:44:29,988
Usually takes
a couple days to clear.

599
00:44:30,072 --> 00:44:31,531
Oh.

600
00:44:33,867 --> 00:44:36,495
Thank you, God.

601
00:44:36,578 --> 00:44:38,997
Thank you.

602
00:44:50,425 --> 00:44:53,929
- Come on.
- Where?

603
00:44:54,012 --> 00:44:55,639
Berenson's been
waiting for you.

604
00:44:55,722 --> 00:44:57,015
Saul's here?

605
00:44:57,099 --> 00:44:58,517
In the SCIF
talking to the president.

606
00:44:58,600 --> 00:44:59,935
Apparently there's
been a breakthrough

607
00:45:00,018 --> 00:45:02,312
in the negotiations.

608
00:45:10,445 --> 00:45:13,115
...our government
to the process.

609
00:45:13,198 --> 00:45:16,034
Without that,
we wouldn't even be here.

610
00:45:18,453 --> 00:45:21,039
<i>Is that you, Ms. Mathison?</i>

611
00:45:21,123 --> 00:45:22,708
<i>Um, it is, sir.</i>

612
00:45:22,791 --> 00:45:23,542
Glad you could join us.

613
00:45:23,625 --> 00:45:26,545
And it's nice
to finally meet you.

614
00:45:26,628 --> 00:45:28,880
Thank you, sir.

615
00:45:28,964 --> 00:45:31,550
- Hello, Carrie.
- David.

616
00:45:31,633 --> 00:45:32,634
<i>We were just
discussing next steps.</i>

617
00:45:32,718 --> 00:45:36,138
<i>To catch you up,
Haissam Haqqani has agreed</i>

618
00:45:36,221 --> 00:45:37,389
in principle to the terms
and the timelines

619
00:45:37,472 --> 00:45:40,559
laid out
in the Doha Framework.

620
00:45:40,642 --> 00:45:43,020
Not only that,
he's committed to a ceasefire.

621
00:45:43,103 --> 00:45:43,895
That should buy us some time

622
00:45:43,979 --> 00:45:46,398
to hash out
the outstanding issues.

623
00:45:46,481 --> 00:45:49,818
One of which is to sell this
peace to the American people.

624
00:45:49,901 --> 00:45:53,030
<i>Well, I think the prospect
