627
00:45:57,909 --> 00:45:59,995
made to look like we're
capitulating to terrorists.

628
00:46:00,078 --> 00:46:03,331
<i>Seeing as you were one of
the architects of the policy,</i>

629
00:46:03,415 --> 00:46:05,459
<i>we thought you might
have some ideas.</i>

630
00:46:07,586 --> 00:46:08,962
Well, I can tell you

631
00:46:09,046 --> 00:46:11,131
what Elizabeth Keane
was planning to do.

632
00:46:11,214 --> 00:46:13,258
<i>Get out in front
of the debate.</i>

633
00:46:13,341 --> 00:46:14,885
Come here to Afghanistan
and make the case

634
00:46:14,968 --> 00:46:16,428
directly to the men and women

635
00:46:16,511 --> 00:46:19,264
who put their lives
on the line every day.

636
00:46:19,347 --> 00:46:21,641
You're talking about
taking a secret trip,

637
00:46:21,725 --> 00:46:24,019
making a surprise announcement?

638
00:46:24,102 --> 00:46:25,020
<i>Followed by
a joint press conference</i>

639
00:46:25,103 --> 00:46:27,939
<i>with President Daoud
at the Arg Palace.</i>

640
00:46:29,024 --> 00:46:29,775
Hmm.

641
00:46:29,858 --> 00:46:31,359
I'm just saying,
win over the military,

